  "content": "\n  );\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace\ngit add tools/corvia-dashboard/src/components/DocumentReader.tsx\ngit commit -m \"feat(dashboard): add DocumentReader side panel with metadata badges and neighbor cards\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2.7: Refactor `GraphView` to split-panel layout with entry-level interaction\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `tools/corvia-dashboard/src/components/GraphView.tsx`\n\nThis is the largest task. The current `GraphView.tsx` (754 lines) renders cluster-based force simulation. We need to:\n\n1. Add a split-panel layout (graph left, reader right)\n2. Add entry-level node rendering inside clusters\n3. Wire click/hover interactions\n4. Integrate `GraphControls`, `DocumentReader`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add imports and state for the new components**\n\nAt the top of `GraphView.tsx`, add:\n\n```tsx\nimport { DocumentReader } from \"./DocumentReader\";\nimport { GraphControls } from \"./GraphControls\";\n```\n\nAdd new state variables in the component:\n\n```tsx\nconst [selectedEntryId, setSelectedEntryId] = useState<string | null>(null);\nconst [hoveredNodeId, setHoveredNodeId] = useState<string | null>(null);\nconst [filters, setFilters] = useState<{\n  contentRole: string | null;\n  sourceOrigin: string | null;\n  depth: number;\n}>({ contentRole: null, sourceOrigin: null, depth: 2 });\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Wrap the canvas in a split-panel layout**\n\nChange the component's return JSX to use a two-column layout:\n\n```tsx\nreturn (\n  <div class=\"graph-split-panel\">\n    <div class={`graph-panel ${selectedEntryId ? \"graph-panel--narrow\" : \"\"}`}>\n      <GraphControls\n        onFilterChange={setFilters}\n        availableRoles={[...new Set(data?.nodes.map(n => n.content_role).filter(Boolean) as string[])]}",
